info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Computes an operation between the values in the same position of multiple input measures. 

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are pairs of:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.

- measure : input measure. This argument can be specified multiple times.
- oph_operation: type of operation
		-- 'sum' : compute the sum;
		-- 'avg' : compute the average;
		-- 'mul' : compute the product;
		-- 'max' : compute the maximum;
		-- 'min' : compute the minimum;
		-- 'arg_max' : return the index of the position associated with the maximum value;
		-- 'arg_min' : return the index of the position associated with the minimum value;

- missingvalue : value to be considered as missing value; by default it is NAN (for 'oph_double' and 'oph_float').

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
oph_operation_array('OPH_DOUBLE|OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',oph_operation, a.measure,b.measure,c.measure,missingvalue)
